## ⚙️ Installation

### 1️⃣ Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/project-report-generator.git
cd project-report-generator
```

### 2️⃣ Create Virtual Environment (Optional)

```bash
python -m venv venv
```

Activate the environment:

#### Windows

```bash
venv\Scripts\activate
```

#### Linux / Mac

```bash
source venv/bin/activate
```

---

## 📦 Install Required Packages

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## ▶️ Run the Application

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

---

## 🔑 Configure Gemini API Key

Replace the API key inside the code:

```python
client = genai.Client(api_key="YOUR_API_KEY")
```

⚠️ Never expose your API key publicly.

---

## 📄 How It Works

1. User uploads a `.docx` project document.
2. The document text is extracted.
3. Gemini AI processes the content.
4. AI generates a structured project report summary.
5. User can download the generated report as a `.docx` file.

